# Skill Routing

Before specialized work, check `.agents/skills/` and read the matching `SKILL.md`. Use the narrowest applicable skill first.

## Common Routes

- Ledger, VAT, reconciliation, audit: `auditing`
- Migrations/schema/indexes: `safe-database-migrations`
- SQL performance: `sql-optimization-patterns` or `postgresql-optimization`
- Financial tests: `fintech-test-driven-development`
- Redis locks/idempotency cache: `redis-caching-and-locks`
- API/webhooks: `api-design-principles`
- Security/PII/auth: `security-best-practices`
- Wallet UI: `frontend-design`, `tailwind-design-system`, `accessibility-compliance`
- Admin portal: `admin-portal-builder`
- Scheduled jobs: `background-jobs-and-cron`
- OCR/ML: `local-ai-and-ocr-pipelines`

Skills add depth; rules remain project law. If a skill conflicts with rules, follow the rules and update the skill/docs.
